pullRequest.title: Make page calculation in bytes on eviction

commit.message: Make page calculation in bytes on eviction

nodes.bodyText: Do we want hashmap or just a page object that has the size?
I think we need a loop here where we evict data, since there is no guarantee one victim is sufficient?
Unrelated question - in some places we do operation first then evictor update and in others we do evictor update then operation, what is the reasoning?

commit.message: Merge branch 'lite' of github.com:Alluxio/alluxio into lite_bytes

nodes.bodyText: I changed the behavior here a bit: if page to insert exists, it returns false now
now we consistently update page store first followed by updating evictor
Let's test with real implementation of MetaStore and PageStore instead the mock. FYI
